MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut in the WA8 postcode area of Widnes, affecting properties in Heathfield Park and the surrounding area. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at 10.55am. Our engineers have arrived on site in the area and are investigating the cause of the fault.  Our team will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible by 2.30pm. We will update this message if this information changes. MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut in the KA7 postcode area of Ayr, affecting properties in Kennedy Drive and surrounding streets. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at 9.38am. Repairs are taking longer than expected as our engineers are now carrying out a complex repair on the underground cable network, caused by a third party near Perryston Lodge and our team are now working to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible by 2pm. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 11.51am on Thursday 29th April 2021.

MAIN_MESSAGE: There is an unplanned power cut affecting the LL23 postcode area of Bala. It will be necessary for our engineers to carry out an emergency shutdown at 10.30am due to tree cutting. Our team will be carrying out repair work safely on the overhead network and this may affect the supply to your property. We will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible, and we expect the power to be restored by 3pm. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 9.28am on 29th of April 2021.
